<br>
I'm normally the only mage going along on our raids.  I need to know how to go about providing a continuous mana supply to clerics on the larger battles we'll be doing soon.<br>
<br>
Using T-Rods and a healer, I can go from 20m to FM very quickly, at the expense of the healer's mana.  Once I'm FM, I can drop rods again for clerics, but again, somebody is using mana to heal the clerics.  I know there is a way, but my brain is just too muddled here to do the math, and figure out how to provide a constant supply of mana for our clerics.  If we can't figure out how to keep the clerics from going OOM after 3-5 minutes, we're not going to get very far.<br>
<br>
Can someone help explain to me exactly what's needed to provide continuous mana to our clerics, and nukers if possible.<br>
<br>
We're ready to do some test runs in the arena, lining up clerics, with a &quot;complete heal&quot; victim to accept complete heals on a rotation from our cleric squad, and back up healers.  I just don't know what the best strategy to use is here.  Who gets rods?  Who heals who?  Can we keep a continuous mana supply going?  Or are we limited to just delaying the OOM for the clerics?<br>
<br>
Thanks, and sorry for the long post!<br>
<br>
- Maige <p><b>Maige Denugget</b><br>Master of the Elements<br>
